# Scenario: WRONG APN (SIMCom dialect) — SIMCom SIM7600G-H. Customer set APN
# to "mobiledata" (probably a leftover from a tablet config) instead of
# "hologram". Same fault class as fixture 05 but on a different vendor and
# with a different error code path: this module returns +CME ERROR: 100
# rather than a bare ERROR for PDP activation failure. Tests whether the
# wrong_apn rule still fires (it relies on +CGACT being errored AND either
# wrong APN string OR +CEER cause 33).
# Expected SE diagnosis: APN mismatch.
# Customer guidance: AT+CGDCONT=1,"IP","hologram"; bounce CFUN.

AT
OK
ATI
SIMCOM_Ltd
SIMCOM_SIM7600G-H
Revision:LE20B04SIM7600G-H
OK
AT+CPIN?
+CPIN: READY
OK
AT+CFUN=1
OK
AT+CGDCONT?
+CGDCONT: 1,"IP","mobiledata","",0,0,0,0
OK
AT+CSQ
+CSQ: 22,99
OK
AT+COPS?
+COPS: 0,0,"AT&T",8
OK
AT+CEREG?
+CEREG: 0,1
OK
AT+CGATT?
+CGATT: 1
OK
AT+CGACT=1,1
+CME ERROR: 100
AT+CEER
+CEER: "Activation reject"," cause 33: requested service option not subscribed"
OK
